ng GPIO pins for inputs.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Establish a machine to machine communication protocol.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Learn how to design an IoT interaction between a sensor and an acuator.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Materials<\/span><\/h1>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Personal Computer<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 x Wemos D1 Mini microcontrollers (ESP8266)<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 x 2.5A USB Power Supply with micro USB Cable<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 x breadboard<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 x Ultrasonic Sensor HC-SR04 <\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 x Red LED<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 x Yellow LED<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 x Green LED<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">3 x 220 \u03a9 Resistor (<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">RR<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">BlBl<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Br<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">) <\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Arduino IDE<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fritzing<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jump wires<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Soldering iron<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Solder<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">GPIO pinout guide<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">References<\/span><\/h1>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The following resources were used in this lab:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/howtomechatronics.com\/tutorials\/arduino\/ultrasonic-sensor-hc-sr04\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">https:\/\/howtomechatronics.com\/tutorials\/arduino\/ultrasonic-sensor-hc-sr04\/<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> &#8211; Great tutorial on how to use Ultrasonic Sensor HC-SR04<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/randomnerdtutorials.com\/complete-guide-for-ultrasonic-sensor-hc-sr04\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">https:\/\/randomnerdtutorials.com\/complete-guide-for-ultrasonic-sensor-hc-sr04\/<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> &#8211; Another great resource explaining how Ultrasonic Sensor HC-SR04 works.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/techtutorialsx.com\/2016\/07\/17\/esp8266-http-get-requests\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">https:\/\/techtutorialsx.com\/2016\/07\/17\/esp8266-http-get-requests\/<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> &#8211; Good resouce to understand how to send a GET request protocol.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.arduino.cc\/reference\/en\/language\/structure\/control-structure\/for\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">https:\/\/www.arduino.cc\/reference\/en\/language\/structure\/control-structure\/for\/<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> &#8211; Arduino documentation about \u201cFor\u201d loop implementation.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.arduino.cc\/reference\/en\/language\/variables\/data-types\/array\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">https:\/\/www.arduino.cc\/reference\/en\/language\/variables\/data-types\/array\